{"key":"processedPost-11571656","value":{"id":11571656,"first":11571528,"last":11574810,"when":1259803481,"utime":"12/03/09 03:24 AM","content":"A small pie tin will give small mushrooms because it's a small, thin substrate.&nbsp; Fresh air is the number one pinning trigger.&nbsp; That's why you <b>must</b> mist or your substrate will dry out. The holes in a shotgun terrarium provide for fresh air, which in turn dries out your substrate.&nbsp; That's how it's supposed to work. Get the substrate wet, and then let it dry out slightly again before misting.&nbsp; This ebb and flow of moisture is what produces the best flushes.<br />RR","title":"Re: Pie tin *fruiting* small shrooms?"}}